app (kernel):
    Main entry point (app, dependency injection [koin])
    Main Navigation of Lumi OS

core (included in all modules):
    System app database and preferences lives here.
    Mini apps have their own database and preferences on their own module.

    data:
        database for user and os (user, wallpaper)
        preferences for user and os itself (user, wallpaper, darkTheme, firstLaunch, etc.)

    domain:
        Result wrapper
        User, Apps, Wallpaper, Contact (domain - business logic)

    presentation:
        Lumi OS theme, system components, shell

system:
    - Apps (or features that lives here) are the one that are expected to exists on all phones.

    boot:
        Setup and Auth

    launcher:
        Home launcher of apps (mini apps and system apps)

    settings:
        System configurations (user level)

    media:
        - camera    (capture images and videos)
        - gallery   (display images captured using our app camera)
        - videos    (display and play captured videos)

    telephony:
        - contacts  (list of contacts isolated to the host)
        - call      (not implemented yet)

miniapps:
    Consists of different optional apps (that can be uninstalled later), just like what a real os
    have.

    notes:
        Note application.

    weather:
        Weather application.

    calendar:
        Calendar application.

    clock:
        Clock application to setup alarm, set timer, and stopwatch.
